Summary

Added a new fast-path benchmark runner: scripts/benchmark_feynman_easy.py. It downloads AI-Feynman example1–3, samples rows, and runs fast-path only.
Extended fast-path to support multi-input datasets:
scripts/classifier_fast_path.py: build_basis_from_predictions now accepts 2D x and generates per-variable terms (polynomials, trig, exp/log, sqrt/reciprocal, relativistic forms, Planck terms), plus pairwise products. Rational/cross terms are now per-variable. The periodic×rational refinement is skipped for multi-input.
run_fast_path preserves multi-dimensional x. fast_path_regression accepts 1D or 2D x.
Fixed benchmark runner to allow multi-input and only compute FFT for 1D.
Ran benchmark once; it failed with IndexError due to basis mismatch, then fixed by refactoring the basis to per-variable. Second run was canceled by user.
